<div class="panel panel-default">
<div class="panel-heading"><a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" style="color: #3d4752;" href="#collapseTwo" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2"> <strong> JIRA Server </strong> </a></div>
<div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
<div class="panel-body">

<h3><u>Step 1: Install the Lucidchart Plugin for JIRA</u><br /><br /></h3>
<ol>
<ol>
<li>Your JIRA administrator must install the Lucidchart plugin for JIRA. Navigate to "Administration" on the right side of the JIRA toolbar.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/7femqdausbuhoou/?name=JIRA1.png" alt="JIRA1.png" width="370" /></li>
<li>Click on "Plugins" on the left side of the JIRA toolbar once in the administration panel.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/79u2ektwqpu1vao/?name=JIRA3.png" alt="JIRA3.png" width="422" height="112" /></li>
<li>Select the "Install Plugins" tab and then "Upload Plugin" near the right side. Follow the dialog to upload the Lucidchart plugin. Download the plugin <a style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" href="https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.lucidchart.jira.plugins.lucid-jira" target="_blank">here</a>.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/njcpmqqx9pld7h4/?name=JIRA2.png" alt="JIRA2.png" width="564" height="96" /></li>
<li>Once uploaded, navigate to the "Manage My Plugins" tab, click "Lucidchart Plugin," and then "Configure" to fill in the key and secret for your organization.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/emmjavxqzeu063k/?name=JIRA4.png" alt="JIRA4.png" width="575" height="188" /></li>
<li>To obtain the key and secret, you must be the administrator for your organization in Lucidchart. If you are the Lucidchart Administrator, click <a style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" href="https://www.lucidchart.com/teams">here</a> to obtain your key and secret and then navigate to "Manage JIRA" on the right side panel.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/e5xvjbjyx7fabpw/?name=JIRA5.png" alt="JIRA5.png" /><br /><br /></li>
<li><span style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;">Generate a key and secret on the </span><a style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" href="http://www.lucidchart.com/teams" target="_blank">Team page</a><span style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;"> in Lucidchart.<br /><br /></span><img style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" src="/attachments/token/zxoibeyggbp2yxk/?name=JIRA6.png" alt="JIRA6.png" /></li>
<li>Copy the key and secret into their respective fields in JIRA and click Save.<br /><br /><img src="/attachments/token/nnuov5slrf8yves/?name=Screen+Shot+2013-06-05+at+10.24.35+AM.png" alt="Screen_Shot_2013-06-05_at_10.24.35_AM.png" width="370" /></li>
</ol>
</ol>
</div>
<hr />
<h3 class="grid_6 omega"><u>Step 2: Adding, drawing, and exiting a diagram</u></h3>
<h3 class="grid_6 omega"> Adding a diagram</h3>
<div class="grid_6 omega">
<div class="grid_6 alpha">
<ol>
<ol>
<li>Select Insert Lucidchart Diagram from the More Actions drop-down menu at the top of your issue in <a href="https://www.lucidchart.com/pages/tour/jira">JIRA</a>.<img src="https://cdn-lucidchart-com.s3.amazonaws.com/jira-insert-0.png" alt="" width="290" /></li>
<li>You'll be then have the option to begin a new Lucidchart document, open an existing Lucidchart document, or directly <a style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" title="Import Visio File" href="http://support.lucidchart.com/entries/21604324-Import-export-Visio-files" target="_blank">import a Visio file</a>. You can learn more about starting new documents and opening existing documents in our <a style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;" href="http://support.lucidchart.com/categories/20063795-Tutorials">tutorials</a>. Selecting a document takes you directly to the Lucidchart editor.<br /><br /><img src="http://support.lucidchart.com/attachments/token/b6xtnyekowygsdz/?name=cop6.png" alt="cop6.png" width="518" height="214" /></li>
</ol>
</ol>
</div>
<hr />
<h3><u>Drawing in the Lucidchart editor</u></h3>
<div class="grid_6 alpha">
<ol>
<ol>
<li>The Lucidchart editor is where where all the magic happens. <a href="http://support.lucidchart.com/entries/21605619-Get-familiar-with-the-Lucidchart-editor">This short tutorial</a> explains the basic components of what you see when you open a document - the canvas, property bar, toolbox, dock, and collaboration bar (click the image to learn more).<br /><br /><a href="http://support.lucidchart.com/entries/21605619-Get-familiar-with-the-Lucidchart-editor" target="_blank"><img src="http://support.lucidchart.com/attachments/token/egxe1pm5ef9g2ug/?name=LucidChart_Editor_Overview18.png" alt="LucidChart_Editor_Overview18.png" width="543" height="304" /></a></li>
</ol>
</ol>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="grid_6 alpha">
<h3><u>Exiting the Lucidchart editor</u></h3>
<ol>
<ol>
<li>When you are finished editing your document in the Lucidchart editor, click the "Return to JIRA" button in the upper right corner to return to JIRA. Your diagram will be automatically added or updated.<br /><br /><img src="http://support.lucidchart.com/attachments/token/dsh2ec2hs1dscac/?name=return_to_JIRA_lucidchart.png" alt="return_to_JIRA_lucidchart.png" /></li>
</ol>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
